sentence: (RTTNews) - The Home Depot, Inc. (HD) shares are rising on Tuesday morning trade as major us indices are on the upside Currently the shares are at $245.98, up 1.72 percent from its previous close of $241.88.
The shares have been on a bullish trend since reporting its first-quarter results on trading May 19.
The stock is trading above its 200-day moving average.
The company has suspended the full-year 2020 outlook due to the coronavirus pandemic.
The first-quarter net earnings were down at $2.2 billion, or $2.08 per share, from $2.5 billion or $2.27 per share in the prior year.
Sales for the quarter grew 7.1 percent to $28.3 billion from last year.
Comparable sales were positive 6.4 percent, and comparable sales in the U.S. were 7.5 percent higher.
